[30;1m174 | [0m[35m* `tornado.testing.gen_test` can now be called as ``@gen_test(timeout=60)``[0m
[30;1m175 | [0m[35m  to give some tests a longer timeout than others.[0m
[30;1m176 | [0m[35m* The environment variable ``ASYNC_TEST_TIMEOUT`` can now be set to[0m
[30;1m177 | [0m[35m  override the default timeout for `.AsyncTestCase.wait` and `.gen_test`.[0m

[30;1m167 | [0m[35mstop the `.IOLoop` with the `.IOLoop.run_sync` method. This is often[0m
[30;1m168 | [0m[35mused to start the ``main`` function of a batch-oriented program::[0m

[30;1m8 | [0m[35mTo minimize the cost of concurrent connections, Tornado uses a[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35msingle-threaded event loop.  This means that all application code[0m
[30;1m10 | [0m[35mshould aim to be asynchronous and non-blocking because only one[0m
[30;1m11 | [0m[35moperation can be active at a time.[0m

[30;1m13 | [0m[35mThe terms asynchronous and non-blocking are closely related and are[0m
[30;1m14 | [0m[35moften used interchangeably, but they are not quite the same thing.[0m

[30;1m128 | [0m[35mcallback objects around, but coroutines provide an important[0m
[30;1m129 | [0m[35msimplification by letting you organize your code in the same way you[0m
[30;1m130 | [0m[35mwould if it were synchronous. This is especially important for error[0m

[30;1m183 | [0m[35m     </html>[0m
[30;1m184 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m185 | [0m[35mBy default, we detect the user's locale using the ``Accept-Language``[0m
[30;1m186 | [0m[35mheader sent by the user's browser. We choose ``en_US`` if we can't find[0m
[30;1m187 | [0m[35man appropriate ``Accept-Language`` value. If you let user's set their[0m
[30;1m188 | [0m[35mlocale as a preference, you can override this default locale selection[0m
[30;1m189 | [0m[35mby overriding `.RequestHandler.get_user_locale`:[0m
[30;1m190 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m272 | [0m[35mand start it with ``python -m tornado.autoreload myserver.py`` to catch[0m
[30;1m273 | [0m[35many syntax errors or other errors at startup.[0m
[30;1m274 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m275 | [0m[35mReloading loses any Python interpreter command-line arguments (e.g. ``-u``)[0m
[30;1m276 | [0m[35mbecause it re-executes Python using `sys.executable` and `sys.argv`.[0m

[30;1m11 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m12 | [0m[35m`Tornado <https://www.tornadoweb.org>`_ is a Python web framework and[0m
[30;1m13 | [0m[35masynchronous networking library, originally developed at `FriendFeed[0m
[30;1m14 | [0m[35m<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FriendFeed>`_.  By using non-blocking network I/O, Tornado[0m
[30;1m15 | [0m[35mcan scale to tens of thousands of open connections, making it ideal for[0m
[30;1m16 | [0m[35m`long polling <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Push_technology#Long_polling>`_,[0m
